The BK-channel in the ‘Working model’ (Borg-Graham, 1998) is a 3-state Markov model that can be in the open state (O), closed state (C) or inactivated state (I). The voltage dependence of the transition rates from states i to j is of the form: rij(V) = (ômin + ((ômax − ômin)¢ + exp((V − V½)Ïk))¢)¢. Here, the inverse values of ômin and ômax represent the upper and lower bounds, respectively, of rij(V). The parameters V½ and k are similar to those used in the extended Hodgkin-Huxley model. The parameters (ômin, ômax, V½, k) of the transition rates in the original model were modified according to Table 1, to make ICT transient during depolarizing voltage-clamp steps. Note that the C O rate transition depends on [Ca¥] and is given by the

